Nigeria Central Bank Calls for Infrastructure Fund, ThisDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-03-02T08:39:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/nigeria-central-bank-calls-for-infrastructure-fund-thisday-says.html
  Nigeria ’s central bank is pushing
for the creation of an infrastructure fund to finance investment
in road and rail links,  power plants  and a gas network,  ThisDay 
reported, citing bank Governor Lamido Sanusi.  Africa’s most populous nation needs to invest $100 billion
over the next 10 years in infrastructure, Sanusi said, according
to the Lagos-based newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at 
 dmbachu@bloomberg.net . 